# ENTITY

## BlogPost

### FEATURES

extends = ["SimpleEntity"]

### DESCRIPTION

Blog article entity. Ownership is represented by SimpleEntity security
attributes. `name` stores the URL/SEO slug, and
`contentAttributes.content` stores the canonical HTML article fragment
extracted from full HTML input or accepted directly by `registerPost`. Images
are represented by CNCF BlobAttachment Association rows whose role identifies
primary, cover, thumbnail, gallery, or inline use. Inline `img` tag occurrences
are tracked by `contentAttributes.references`.

Public read/search should expose only posts whose SimpleEntity lifecycle is
`postStatus = published` and `aliveness = alive`. Draft and inactive posts
remain author/admin surfaces.

No Blog-specific persistent attributes are required. The article slug, title,
content, lifecycle state, owner, and security are inherited from SimpleEntity
attributes.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name     | type   | multiplicity | label  | derived |
|----------+--------+--------------+--------+---------|
| authorId | string | ?            | Author | ownerId |

