# COMMAND

## ImportPostTree

### DESCRIPTION

User-facing bulk import command. `fileBundle` is the Web/client transport for a
Blog article file tree. `archiveBlobId` points to a Blob containing the same
tree as a ZIP archive. The tree must contain `META-INF/blog.yaml`; metadata in
that file is authoritative, and missing values may fall back to the HTML head.
`treeRootPath` is the local development-driver input for an already expanded
tree.

The entry HTML may be a full HTML document. BlogComponent parses it through CNCF
standard HTML tree values, extracts the article fragment, resolves relative
image paths, and calls `RegisterBlogPost`.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name            | type     | multiplicity |
|-----------------+----------+--------------|
| fileBundle      | filebundle | ?          |
| archiveBlobId   | entityid | ?            |
| treeRootPath    | string   | ?            |
| entryHtmlPath   | string   | ?            |
| publish         | boolean  | ?            |

## RegisterBlogPost

### DESCRIPTION

Lower-level bulk registration command. `content` is a normalized HTML fragment.
`entityImages` represents thumbnail/cover/gallery style Entity images. Images
embedded in the HTML content are extracted into `contentAttributes.references`
and linked as inline BlobAttachment associations.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name            | type                | multiplicity |
|-----------------+---------------------+--------------|
| slug            | string              | 1            |
| title           | string              | ?            |
| content         | string              | 1            |
| publish         | boolean             | ?            |
| description     | string              | ?            |
| canonicalPath   | string              | ?            |
| entityImages    | BlogEntityImageSpec | *            |

## SaveEditorBlogPost

### DESCRIPTION

Editor-facing save command. Author is derived from the authenticated session;
client-supplied author account ids are ignored.

### ATTRIBUTE

| name        | type     | multiplicity |
|-------------+----------+--------------|
| id          | entityid | ?            |
| slug        | string   | ?            |
| title       | string   | 1            |
| content     | string   | 1            |
| description | string   | ?            |
| publish     | boolean  | ?            |

